                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 294/525: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-06-14T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1926—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>173. For Hill. H–59. Tour H–113, June 5, 2 p.m. The Department perceives no
                    objection to agreement extending over more than the third annuity on the terms
                    stated in paragraph 4 your telegram.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
